context: The lights turn on as it notices motion in the room as you walk by its sensors.

stimuli: A group of teenagers run up to egg your house.

context: I am walking from the bedroom to the kitchen and back again.
stimuli: I get up in the night to get a drink of water.

context: when crawling into the room he will trigger the light if it works.

context: A pet is recognized as a non-human movement.

stimuli: I am only briefly walking through the room
response: The lights turn to dim for 60 seconds then fade back off.

context: If for example, I decide to take a short nap while watching television.
stimuli: I clap my hands to deactivate the last preset and turn the system off.
response: System should respond to the clap command and turn lights off until another clap command id performed to resume the last preset.

context: Multiple people in a room engaging in various activities
stimuli: Multiple people in a room
response: Smart lights should find a configuration balance and provide neutral lighting to make the users' differing activities as enjoyable as possible

context: Room is quiet and no movement after 6pm
stimuli: No movement in the room for 15 minutes
response: Lights automatically fade off and room goes dark.

context: House detects movement and is alerted of the presence of the intruder
stimuli: Creature or intruder enters the yard of the house

context: no noise and movement

context: A sensor detects movement in my bedroom.

context: It is night time and there are no lights on inside or outside the house, and the person is an authorized person.
stimuli: Someone comes home from work and walks up the driveway.

context: It has been a few hours and the sun has been going down, so the ambient light is reducing.

context: The sound senser detects the foot noise.
stimuli: A person walks on the street near the home.

context: The sensors detect the movement of curtains in a specific time.
stimuli: Person want to have a little sleep during day, he closes his window curtains.

context: Since there is motion at the sink the overhead light should turn on.

context: The front porch lights turn on when motion is detected on the driveway.

context: While the TV is on and presence is detected on the seating area the lights dim.
stimuli: When watching TV the lights in the room should dim.

context: The family is out of town on vacation.
stimuli: No movement in the room.

stimuli: A child is in its bed at bedtime.

context: It is night time. No exterior lights are currently on. No people are outside the house.
stimuli: A large animal such as a dog or deer walk into the yard.

context: It is night time. The exterior lights in the backyard are too bright and interfere with their activities. They want the lights dimmed but not turned completely off. There are people both inside and outside the house. The owner connects via smartphone and selects an option to dim the exterior lights in the back yard.
stimuli: The occupants of the house are enjoying looking at stars on the deck in the backyard.
response: The lights should dim according to the settings selected by the homeowner.

context: The room is dark enough for light to be appropriate.
stimuli: A person walks into a dark room, triggering the motion sensor.
response: The lights turn on.

context: It is dark outside.
stimuli: A person outside the home moves about and triggers the motion sensor.
response: The outside light turns on.

context: A large dog can have more mass than many humans and motion detectors do not compensate for what triggers motion in the room.
stimuli: Large canine enters a dark room during sleeping hours of owners.
response: Owner is able to set sleeping hours inside app settings so as not to trigger unsophisticated motion detectors during off" hours."

context: Advanced motion detector ability triggers software inside the main processing unit.
stimuli: Wild boar (let's say this takes place in Germany) begin to sort through a compost bin outside of an owner's home after dusk.
response: Pattern recognition software analyzes the movement patterns based on the data set download the owner has received for his area, recognizes the pattern a boar makes as it moves about, and does not trigger the outside light as per the owner's custom app settings.  ( I saw a video of a cat door that someone with arduino skills cooked up where he was able to identify his cat versus racoons and such and only unlocked the cat door for his cat based on software.)

context: a person IN the room stands/sit still for the preconfigured amount of time
stimuli: no movement or sound for the pre-configured time
response: the lights start to fade out gradually. if a movement or sound is detected the lights are switching to the preconfigured level. If no movement or sound is detected for a second preconfigured amount of time (t2) the lights fade out completely
